If you wanted a tower defense mobile game, where cute female characters guard a base under your leadership — meet Arknights! This is a game for you if you like to read long story dialogues, collect characters, and gacha system. The player takes the role of the amnesiac “Doctor”, who commands a team of operators. Arknights begins with the doctor being on the verge of death, but the faithful operators save him, and the game is on. You’ll need to defend your base (which is represented as a blue door), prevent crowds of enemies from infiltrating, and strategically place operators on the correct tiles. For example, you need to keep track of how many mobs the character can kill and also keep a balance between melee and range damage dealers when creating a party. Missions are easy to complete only at beginner levels, but further you’ll need upgrades and S-rank characters apart from the strategic positioning in battle. But it’s not that easy: first, you need to obtain the desired characters and then upgrade them. As in any MMO game, there are two options. The first is to save in-game currency long and hard for random gacha rolls and Battle Records to improve operators. The second is to buy Arknights Top Up and get everything at once. For Originium, you can open an unlimited number of packs with operators, and the amount of Sanity will allow you to restore energy and play all day long. Purchasing packs will allow you to get a lot of resources for leveling and upgrading characters, as well as new furniture parts. So it’s almost essential to buy Arknights Top Up for a comfortable gaming experience.
